---
export const prerender = true;
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Notice" description="Privacy Notice — how Hengistbury Investment Partners LLP processes personal data under UK GDPR.">

  <div class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <a href="/disclosures" class="back-link">← Disclosures</a>
      <p class="eyebrow">Regulatory Disclosure</p>
      <h1>Privacy Notice</h1>
      <p class="meta">Hengistbury Investment Partners LLP &mdash; Effective April 2026</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <article class="disclosure-body">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="doc-grid">
        <nav class="doc-toc">
          <ol>
            <li><a href="#controller">Data Controller</a></li>
            <li><a href="#data-collected">Personal Data We Collect</a></li>
            <li><a href="#lawful-basis">Lawful Basis for Processing</a></li>
            <li><a href="#use">How We Use Your Data</a></li>
            <li><a href="#retention">Retention</a></li>
            <li><a href="#rights">Your Rights</a></li>
            <li><a href="#contact">Contact</a></li>
          </ol>
          <div class="toc-footer">
            <a href="/disclosures" class="back-link-sm">All disclosures</a>
          </div>
        </nav>

        <div class="doc-content">
          <section id="controller">
            <h2>1. Data Controller</h2>
            <p>
              Hengistbury Investment Partners LLP (&ldquo;we&rdquo;, &ldquo;us&rdquo;, &ldquo;the Firm&rdquo;), partnership number
              OC365747, with registered office at First Floor, 34 Brook Street, London W1K 5DN,
              is the data controller responsible for your personal information.
            </p>
            <p>
              We process personal data in accordance with the UK General Data Protection
              Regulation (&ldquo;UK GDPR&rdquo;) and the Data Protection Act 2018.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section id="data-collected">
            <h2>2. Personal Data We Collect</h2>
            <p>We may collect and process the following categories of personal data:</p>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Identity data:</strong> name, date of birth, nationality, passport or identity document information;</li>
              <li><strong>Contact data:</strong> address, email address, telephone numbers;</li>
              <li><strong>Financial data:</strong> bank account details, source of wealth, investment experience and objectives;</li>
              <li><strong>Due diligence data:</strong> information collected for the purpose of anti-money laundering (AML) and know-your-customer (KYC) compliance;</li>
              <li><strong>Technical data:</strong> IP address, browser type, operating system and other data collected automatically when you access our website or investor portal;</li>
              <li><strong>Communications data:</strong> emails, meeting notes and other correspondence.</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section id="lawful-basis">
            <h2>3. Lawful Basis for Processing</h2>
            <p>We process personal data on one or more of the following lawful bases:</p>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Contract:</strong> processing is necessary for the performance of a contract to which you are party, or to take steps at your request prior to entering into a contract;</li>
              <li><strong>Legal obligation:</strong> processing is necessary to comply with applicable laws and regulations, including FCA rules, AML legislation and tax requirements;</li>
              <li><strong>Legitimate interests:</strong> processing is necessary for the purposes of our legitimate interests in managing the Firm, communicating with investors and prospective investors, and protecting the security of our systems;</li>
              <li><strong>Consent:</strong> where required by applicable law, we will request your consent before processing your personal data.</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section id="use">
            <h2>4. How We Use Your Data</h2>
            <p>We use personal data for the following purposes:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Managing your investment relationship with the Firm;</li>
              <li>Complying with our regulatory and legal obligations, including AML/KYC checks;</li>
              <li>Communicating with you about your investment, portfolio updates and fund matters;</li>
              <li>Maintaining our books and records;</li>
              <li>Responding to enquiries; and</li>
              <li>Operating and improving our website and investor portal.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
              We do not sell personal data to third parties. We may share data with regulators,
              legal and compliance advisors, auditors, fund administrators, custodians and other
              service providers strictly as necessary to provide our services and meet our
              obligations.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section id="retention">
            <h2>5. Retention</h2>
            <p>
              We retain personal data for as long as necessary to fulfil the purposes for which
              it was collected, including for the purposes of satisfying any legal, regulatory,
              accounting or reporting requirements.
            </p>
            <p>
              In accordance with AML regulations, certain due diligence records are retained
              for a minimum of five years following the end of a business relationship. Other
              records may be retained for longer periods where required by law.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section id="rights">
            <h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
            <p>Under UK GDPR, you have the following rights in relation to your personal data:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>The right to be informed about how your data is used;</li>
              <li>The right of access to your personal data;</li>
              <li>The right to rectification of inaccurate data;</li>
              <li>The right to erasure in certain circumstances;</li>
              <li>The right to restrict processing;</li>
              <li>The right to data portability;</li>
              <li>The right to object to processing based on legitimate interests; and</li>
              <li>Rights in relation to automated decision-making and profiling.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
              To exercise any of your rights, please contact us using the details below. You
              also have the right to lodge a complaint with the Information Commissioner&rsquo;s
              Office (&ldquo;ICO&rdquo;) at <a href="https://ico.org.uk" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">ico.org.uk</a>.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section id="contact">
            <h2>7. Contact</h2>
            <p>
              If you have any questions about this Privacy Notice or how we process your
              personal data, please contact us at:
            </p>
            <address>
              Hengistbury Investment Partners LLP<br />
              First Floor, 34 Brook Street<br />
              London W1K 5DN<br />
              Email: <a href="mailto:info@hengistburypartners.com">info@hengistburypartners.com</a>
            </address>
          </section>

          <div class="doc-footer">
            <p>Effective date: April 2026 &bull; This notice may be updated periodically</p>
            <p>
              Hengistbury Investment Partners LLP &bull; Partnership No: OC365747 &bull;
              Authorised and regulated by the Financial Conduct Authority
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-hero { background: var(--navy); padding: 3rem 0 4rem; }
  .back-link { display: inline-block; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5); font-size: 0.85rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; transition: color 0.2s; }
  .back-link:hover { color: var(--gold); }
  .eyebrow { font-size: 0.75rem; letter-spacing: 0.12em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--gold); font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .page-hero h1 { color: var(--white); margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .meta { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5); font-size: 0.875rem; }
  .disclosure-body { padding: 4rem 0; background: var(--white); }
  .doc-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 220px 1fr; gap: 4rem; align-items: start; }
  .doc-toc { position: sticky; top: 90px; }
  .toc-label { font-size: 0.7rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; font-weight: 600; color: var(--mid-gray); margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .doc-toc ol { list-style: none; border-left: 2px solid var(--border); padding-left: 0; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  .doc-toc a { display: block; padding: 0.45rem 0.75rem; font-size: 0.82rem; color: var(--mid-gray); border-left: 2px solid transparent; margin-left: -2px; line-height: 1.4; transition: color 0.15s, border-color 0.15s; }
  .doc-toc a:hover { color: var(--navy); border-left-color: var(--gold); }
  .toc-footer { border-top: 1px solid var(--border); padding-top: 1rem; }
  .back-link-sm { font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--mid-gray); }
  .back-link-sm:hover { color: var(--gold); }
  .doc-content section { margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  .doc-content h2 { font-size: 1.4rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; padding-bottom: 0.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .doc-content p { color: #444; line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 0.6rem; }
  .doc-content ul { color: #444; padding-left: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; line-height: 1.7; }
  .doc-content li { margin-bottom: 0.25rem; }
  .doc-content a { color: var(--gold); }
  .doc-content a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
  address { font-style: normal; line-height: 1.8; color: #444; }
  .doc-footer { border-top: 1px solid var(--border); padding-top: 2rem; margin-top: 3rem; }
  .doc-footer p { font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--mid-gray); line-height: 1.65; }
  @media (max-width: 768px) { .doc-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } .doc-toc { position: static; } }
</style>
